race.description: Gary Thatcher Memorial F&M Benchmark 64 Handicap
race.comment: PURPLE ROSE (9) speedy mare racing in career best form. No reason she can't make it three-straight victories after running them ragged when saluting at Wyong in good style over 1350m. Well drawn and will prove hard to hold out. PESCHIERA (3) lightly raced mare unlucky not to have a few more wins on the CV. Battled on gamely from the outside barrier when seventh over 1250m at Canterbury. Has a solid second-up record and gets a better run today. OUTTA LINE (7) lightly raced mare with ability resuming from a lengthy break. Gave them a galloping lesson on debut as fav when a slick winner over 1350m at Wyong in a Super Mdn. Looks ready to go with the two solid trials. COMMANDING BELLE (2) good second-up performer who will find this easier after resuming with a battling fifth over 1200m at Rosehill in BM68 grade. Claim helps and has a good record on her home track.
